  <mainDescription>&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Business Process Modelling&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    This practice provides guidelines for how to use BPMN to define and model business processes. The practice prescribes&#xD;
    building a set of model artefacts following the iterative and incremental process paradigm. The main model to construct&#xD;
    is the&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
        href=&quot;./../../../practice.business.business_process_modelling.base-sintef/workproducts/business_process_model_68EE53A2.html&quot;&#xD;
         guid=&quot;_t_xQYOEAEd-uaoNIhpFKqA&quot;>Business process model&lt;/a>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    which defines the business processes of the domain which are relevant to the service-oriented architecture. In addition&#xD;
    to the process model a related&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
        href=&quot;./../../../practice.business.business_process_modelling.base-sintef/workproducts/business_information_model_79DCA1E1.html&quot;&#xD;
         guid=&quot;_xQIN4OEAEd-uaoNIhpFKqA&quot;>Business information model&lt;/a>&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    which defines the business information that are&amp;nbsp;exchanged in the business processes is also prescribed.&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
